@93548 = ~Wand of Summon Insects~
@93549 = ~With activating this wand, it attracts a cloud or swarm of normal insects to attack one enemy of the wielder. This swarm gathers at a point chosen by the wielder, within the spell's range, and attacks a single creature the wielder points to.

For the duration of the spell, the affected creature fights with a -2 penalty to attack rolls and armor class. In addition, each round the victim suffers 2d3 points of damage from insect bites, has a 100% chance of spell failure and it if fails a save vs. poison at +2 it panics and flees from the wielder. If a successful save vs. breath at -2 is made, the target manages to avoid most of the swarm, reducing damage from bites by half and completely negating the spell failure penalty. Magic resistance does not affect this spell.

