//Improved Invisibility
@94008 = ~Wand of Improved Invisibility~
@94009 = ~This wand causes a creature touched to vanish from sight and be undetectable by normal vision or even infravision. Even allies cannot see the invisible creature or its gear, unless these allies can normally see invisible things or employ magic to do so. Items dropped or put down by the invisible creature become visible, items picked up disappear if tucked into the clothing or pouches worn by the creature. Of course, the invisible creature is not magically silenced, and certain other conditions can render the creature detectable.

The invisibility remains in effect until it is magically broken or dispelled. Subtle hints —a shimmering— allow an observant opponent to attack the invisible spell recipient; these traces are only noticeable when specifically looked for (after the invisible character has made <PRO_HISHER> presence known†). The caster can, however, cast defensive spells on <PRO_HIMHER>self and fellow party members.

